OL,5,B      Teletext on the ZX Spectrum      
OL,6,B```````````````````````````````````````
OL,7,BThe Volex TTX2000S is a peripheral for 
OL,8,Bthe ZX Spectrum. It adds the ability to
OL,9,Breceive teletext from up to four UHF TV
OL,10,Bchannels.                              
OL,12,BWhen I got the adapter it wouldn't tune
OL,13,Breliably and needed constant fiddling. 
OL,15,BIn the process of reverse engineering a
OL,16,Bschematic I traced the issue to one of 
OL,17,Bthe ceramic capacitors. I replaced that
OL,18,Bwhich solved the drifting issue but the
OL,19,Bjoy was short lived...                 
OL,20,B``````````````````````````````````1/3``
OL,21,     FZX Spectrum TelesoftwareBp460      
OL,22,B]MD MORE RETRO COMPUTER STUFF p410     
OL,24,AIndexBTelesoftwareCRe-EnthusedFDiscord 
PN,46102
SC,0002
FL,101,460,410,131,4ff,101
OL,1,R      pp0pp00 ``pp0ppp`pp0ppp`pp0      
OL,2,R       5  5 e :"  55 jj  55 jj  %      
OL,3,R          x#dj7#!5 j j55 b#k5      
OL,4,R       /  / / **-,$-,/*,.%-,/*,.%      
OL,5,B      Teletext on the ZX Spectrum      
OL,6,B```````````````````````````````````````
OL,7,BI'd just got the adapter tuning signals
OL,8,Breliably when it suddenly stopped being
OL,9,Bable to decode anything at all.        
OL,11,BSomething had killed the data separator
OL,12,BIC which is an obsolete Plessey chip.  
OL,13,BI was able to buy an entire tube off   
OL,14,Bebay for less than others were selling 
OL,15,Bsingle chips!                          
OL,17,BReplacing the chip once again restored 
OL,18,Bthe adapter to working condition so the
OL,19,Breverse engineering could be completed.
OL,20,B``````````````````````````````````2/3``
OL,21,     FZX Spectrum TelesoftwareBp460      
OL,22,B]MD    VIDEO GAMES NONSENSE P170        
OL,24,AIndexBTelesoftwareCRe-EnthusedFDiscord 
PN,46103
SC,0003
FL,101,460,410,131,4ff,101
OL,1,R      pp0pp00 ``pp0ppp`pp0ppp`pp0      
OL,2,R       5  5 e :"  55 jj  55 jj  %      
OL,3,R          x#dj7#!5 j j55 b#k5      
OL,4,R       /  / / **-,$-,/*,.%-,/*,.%      
OL,5,B      Teletext on the ZX Spectrum      
OL,6,B```````````````````````````````````````
OL,7,BWith the hardware traced out to a full 
OL,8,Bschematic I was able to figure out the 
OL,9,Bprinciple of operation.                
OL,11,BAlas the logic is all implemented in a 
OL,12,Bsemi-custom NEC gate array so can only 
OL,13,Bbe analysed as a black box.            
OL,15,BDespite this setback I've been able to 
OL,16,Binfer plenty from the signals placed on
OL,17,Bthe buses though, along with the firm- 
OL,18,Bware which I have created a commented  
OL,19,Bdisassembly for.                       
OL,20,B``````````````````````````````````3/3``
